<h1>Refreshing a Project</h1>
<p>The project can be refreshed through two ways: Refresh Automatically or
Refresh Project.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>In the <b>Refresh Automatically</b> option, the project is refreshed always
that when the user returns the focus to the application. The refreshing process
is performed when a use case document is updated and saved, or an artifact is
added in or removed from the project (e.g, manually remove an artifact outside
the TaRGeT). To disable this option, click in it in the menu bar.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="Images/refreshAutomatically.PNG" border="0" width="354" height="155"></p>
<p><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</b>&nbsp;</p>
<p>In the <b>Refresh Project </b>option, the project is refresh just when the
user click in this option in the menu bar or press its byway CTRL+R.</p>
<p><img src="Images/refreshProject.PNG" border="0" width="354" height="155"></p>
<p><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</b>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The refreshing includes the reloading of some documents (when necessary), and
the updating of the <a href="TaRGeTWorkspace.htm">TaRGeT Workspace</a> contents.
During the refreshing, a progress bar is displayed.</p>
<img alt="Refreshing Progress Bar" src="Images/refreshProgressBar.PNG" width="451" height="189"><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</b>
<p>The refreshing will display <a href="UseCaseDocError.htm">errors</a> in the
error view in case of a use case document is damaged when updated.</p>

